item.description:
I use DevRant, a social for rant by developer. One day I find this rant.
 Some empty-headed helpdesk girl skipped into our office yesterday afternoon, despite the big scary warning signs glued to the door.
&ldquo;Hey, when I log in on my phone, the menu is looking weird&rdquo;
&ldquo;Uh&hellip; look at my beard&rdquo;
&ldquo;What&rdquo;
&ldquo;Just look at this beard!&rdquo;
&ldquo;Uh&hellip;. OK&rdquo;
&ldquo;Does this look like a perfectly groomed beard&rdquo;

Microsoft now own Github. From this we need to make some talk about the question which all the open source community is doing: &ldquo;Whas are going to change into the OpenSource comunity or into the public code?&rdquo;
Many developer thinks about this and say something similar to &ldquo;I do not want to risc my project so goodby&rdquo; and the move to GitLab all theire code.
GitHub imports to GitLab are still going up!
